Business Development for Marketplace
Responsibilities
Source, select and purchase appropriate brand merchandise, in a required time frame and in line with the company merchandise strategy.Identify key seasonal trends relevant to the Indonesia marketMaintaining and coordinate with suppliers.In conjunction with the planner, monitor and take accountability of weekly sales and profit and responding to the product performances with effective merchandise strategies.Working with a buying plan, to ensure maximisation of sales and inventory control.Conducting periodical reviews to include missed opportunities and further potential successes.Negotiation of buying and settlement termsProactively conduct competitor analysis to ensure a competitive advantage.Proactively recommend initiatives to continuously improve product ranging. Requirements: At least 2 years recent experience as a merchandiser and  purchasing in one or two particular product categoriesExcellent ability with excelExceptional relationship management and negotiation skillsA well developed eye for spotting winners and identifying product opportunitiesGreat time management skillsA dynamic personality, high level of enthusiasm and commitmentResults driven and target orientedCan work under pressure Please send your CV directly to career@zalora.co.id
